                <h1>Rite Aid Background Check: What You Need to Know</h1>
                <p>Rite Aid conducts thorough background checks on potential employees to ensure a safe and reliable workforce. This process typically includes criminal history, employment verification, and, in some cases, drug screening. Applicants can expect the check to take several days, as Rite Aid prioritizes integrity and customer safety in hiring.</p>
